# Git Commit Message Template
# 
# [Optional: type] Brief description (50 characters or less)
#
# More detailed explanation if needed. Wrap it to 72 characters.
# Focus on what was changed and why, not who helped with the change.
#
# IMPORTANT RULES:
# - NEVER mention Claude, AI assistant, or any AI tool names
# - NEVER include "Generated with [tool]" or "Co-Authored-By: AI"  
# - Keep messages professional and focused on technical changes
# - Write as if you (the human developer) made all the changes
#
# Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore